# PR Before Deploy

Deploy workflows (`deploy-azure`, frontend Azure/Cloudflare) are gated on merging a green PR. They MUST NOT be triggered by pushing directly to `main`.

## Deploy gate

```
branch → PR → CI green → merge → deploy workflows auto-trigger
```

`deploy-azure` runs on `src/**`, `Cargo.toml`, or `Dockerfile` changes.  
Frontend deploy workflows run on merges to `main` when configured.  
They are triggered automatically — never run them manually ahead of a merge.

## Why this matters

Direct pushes to `main` have caused production outages in this repo:
- The `Column avatar_png does not exist` degraded-mode startup was caused by merging without a migration-verified PR
- The `deploy-frontend` workflow failed silently on every push for months because no PR CI caught the broken `cache: npm` setting

See `agent-branching.mdc` for the full branch/worktree workflow.
